TITLE: Commerce Secretary Raimondo pressed on Biden looking 'flat-footed' on inflation, baby formula shortage
SUMMARY: CNN's Jake Tapper pressed Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo on Sunday's "State of the Union" about the Biden administration looking "flat-footed" on inflation.

TITLE: US says Russia isn't serious about allowing Ukraine grain exports
SUMMARY: Russian officials are not operating in good faith in negotiations with the U.N. over allowing Ukraine to make grain exports through the Black Sea, U.S. officials say.

TITLE: Mets' Max Scherzer bit by dog while on the mend, downplays incident
SUMMARY: Max Scherzer, already on the IL with an oblique injury, was bit by his dog but made clear it wasn't affecting his rehab. The pitcher called the bite a “non-story.”

TITLE: US, South Korea conduct joint navy drills ahead of possible North Korea nuclear test
SUMMARY: Officials in the U.S. and the Indo-Pacific region have warned that North Korea is set to conduct its first nuclear test after satellite images showed construction at a facility.

TITLE: DC suspect wanted for armed hijacking of ambulance as EMS treated patient
SUMMARY: The DC Metro Police Department is seeking the identity of a man accused of displaying a handgun and threatening EMS personnel before making off with an ambulance Saturday.

TITLE: NYC corrections captain at Rikers dies in Dominican Republic after Brazilian butt lift from bogus doc: report
SUMMARY: A 49-year-old New York City Corrections Captain at Rikers Island died in the Dominican Republic after receiving Brazilian butt lift surgery from infamous Dr. Hector Cabral.

TITLE: Missouri firefighters rescue 7 people trapped up to 40 feet in air on carnival ride
SUMMARY: Firefighters in Kirkwood, Missouri, rescued seven passengers who were trapped on a carnival ride during a fundraising event for a local Catholic church on Friday night.

TITLE: Boris Johnson faces 'no confidence' vote after polls show he would lose election held today: Report
SUMMARY: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson would lose parliament as well as his own seat as a minister if the government held an election, new polling data showed.

TITLE: French Open 2022: Rafael Nadal dominates Casper Ruud for championship
SUMMARY: Rafael Nadal picked up his 14th French Open title with a 6-3, 6-3, 6-0 straight-set victory over Norway's Casper Ruud Sunday. It 's his 22nd major title overall.

TITLE: Dem Sen. Chris Murphy insists Biden not get involved with bipartisan gun negotiations
SUMMARY: U.S. Sen. Chris Murphy insisted that Democrats and Republicans negotiate without President Biden to find how Congress can reach a compromise on gun reform legislation.

TITLE: Chattanooga shooting leaves 3 dead and 14 injured, some struck by fleeing cars
SUMMARY: A shooting in downtown Chattanooga has left three dead and 14 injured, with some of the injuries coming when bystanders were struck by the suspects fleeing vehicle.

TITLE: Tropical Storm Alex heads toward Bermuda with high winds
SUMMARY: Tropical Storm Alex moved toward Bermuda Sunday, prompting tropical storm warnings in the area after passing Florida as the first Atlantic hurricane of the season.

TITLE: Cats in the house: How to bring a new feline into your family successfully
SUMMARY: June is National Adopt a Cat Month (also known as Adopt a Shelter Cat Month) — and Fox News Digital shares expert tips on welcoming a new cat into the home.

TITLE: French Open champ Iga Swiatek powers through strange makeup question after victory
SUMMARY: Poland's Iga Swiatek breezed by American Coco Gauff in the French Open final Saturday but was met with a strange question in the post-match press conference.

TITLE: Queen’s Platinum Jubilee wraps up with London street pageant
SUMMARY: Queen Elizabeth II's Platinum Jubilee celebrating her 70 years on the throne will come to an end in London on Sunday, capping off with a colorful street pageant.

TITLE: Wall Street Journal slams media for heaping credibility on anti-DeSantis whistleblower
SUMMARY: The WSJ editorial board criticized the media for giving a platform to Rebekah Jones, who claimed in 2020 that she was fired for refusing to change COVID data in Florida.

TITLE: Philadelphia mayor responds to mass shooting that left 3 dead, 11 wounded; suspects still at large
SUMMARY: Philadelphia Democratic Mayor Jim Kenney issued a statement responding to a mass shooting that killed three and wounded 11 others Saturday. The suspects still remain at large.

TITLE: Pizza Hut facing boycott calls after promoting 'drag kids' book for kindergartners
SUMMARY: Pizza Hut is facing boycott calls after promoting a book for kids as young as pre-K that "celebrates drag kids" for the company's  "Book It!" reading incentive program.

TITLE: Utah teen tackles potential armed robber at restaurant, police say
SUMMARY: A 17-year-old employee at Durango's Mexican Grill in St. George, Utah, tackled a potentially armed suspect during an attempted robbery on Friday night, authorities said.

TITLE: Aaron Judge's 21st dinger keeps him on pace with Yankees greats
SUMMARY: Aaron Judge helped the Yankees secure a 3-0 win over the Detroit Tigers on Saturday and is keeping pace in the home run race with some of the greats. He's got 21 so far.
